cpunodebind  

Run a process on CPUs on a specific NUMA node. This does not isolate cores at the kernel level. You can pass the following parameter in your systemd unit file. Example below is for httpd. 

cat /usr/lib/systemd/system/httpd.service | grep ExecStart 
 
ExecStart=/usr/bin/numactl --cpunodebind=0 /usr/sbin/httpd $OPTIONS -DFOREGROUND 
 

 

physcpubind 

Run a process on CPUs on a specific set of cores. This does not isolate cores at the kernel level. 

cat /usr/lib/systemd/system/httpd.service | grep ExecStart 
 
ExecStart=/usr/bin/numactl --physcpubind=0,1,2,3 /usr/sbin/httpd $OPTIONS â€“DFOREGROUND 

 

 

membind 

Run a process on memory on a specific NUMA node. You can pass the following parameter in your systemd unit file. Example below is for httpd. 

cat /usr/lib/systemd/system/httpd.service | grep ExecStart 
 
ExecStart=/usr/bin/numactl --cpunodebind=0 --membind=0 /usr/sbin/httpd $OPTIONS -DFOREGROUND
